Devon and Cornwall Police is offering children the opportunity to choose the official name of its newest tractor.Children are asked to submit their chosen name to the force via the Devon and Cornwall Police website.The competition is open until midnight on 9 June and the winner will be announced at Woofstock Festival on 15 June.In 2023, a police tractor was named Optimus Crime by four-year-old Reuben.
Entrants must be living in Devon, Cornwall or the Isles of Scilly and be aged 12 or under at the time the competition closes on 9 June.The new tractor will be used as an engagement tool by the rural affairs team at agricultural events this summer.
